My first instinct is to say, &quot;Yeah! We've got to stop Hussein from getting weapons of mass destruction!&quot; But then I wonder, just what criteria are we using? I mean, why can some countries have them but not other countries? Who gets to decide that? I'd prefer that NO countries had weapons of mass destruction, but the cat's already out of that particular bag.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also read my post above if you want to know why Iraq...<br>
