We went to war when he invaded Kuwait. Who has he invaded since then? No one. That war was for the purpose of liberating Kuwait, wasn't it? So who are we going to war to liberate now...?<br>
<br>
I admit that I was flabbergasted that we didn't get rid of Hussein back then, but nothing new has happened since to make him deserve being taken out any more than he did then, when we chose not to. So why choose to now?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>We had to step in and smack him down. We let him live. Now we've assumed responsibility for the asshole...<br>
