At last, we agree on something. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We helped him come to power, we helped him stay in power, and we helped arm his military. So yeah, we damned well should take responsibility for him.<br>
<br>
But it would have been a hell of a lot less trouble if we'd been responsible about who we helped and what we did in Iraq in the first place. It's stupid to make a deal with the devil, then act outraged when you get jabbed with his pitchfork.<br>
